      },
      "date": "2017-06-08 11:32:42.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\nBesides the build failure, there are some flaws in the algorithm used to batch requests according to their priority: (from most to least important)\n\n- The traversal of spd->requests becomes too costful when cdt->max_requests is large and spd->requests is almost full;\n- Non-prioritized requests cannot be replaced in spd->requests, even if they are beyond the barrier;\n- prioritized requests fill the buffer from the \"right side\" whereas documentation shows they should fill the buffer from the left side (and vice-versa for non-priotized requests).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
