          "tz": 120
        },
        "subject": "LU-8324 hsm: prioritize HSM requests",
        "message": "LU-8324 hsm: prioritize HSM requests\n\nThis patch separates the coordinator's implementation from the way\nit processes requests stored in its llog. This last part is now\nhandled by a scan policy. A scan policy implements a vector of 3\noperations to init the policy's internal structure, process the\nstored requests, and exit cleanly.\n\nA new scan policy is defined: \"priority_policy\".\nThe working principles of the policy can be found in the comments of\n\"mdt_coordinator_priority_policy.c\". Interactive HSM requests\n(HSM_RESTORE and HSM_CANCEL) will basically be prioritized over other\ntypes of requests (HSM_NOOP, HSM_ARCHIVE, and HSM_REMOVE).\n\nScan policies can be dynamically switched by writing the name of\nthe policy to use in the proc file \"scan_policy\" (which can be found\nin the hsm proc directory).\n\nThis patch also adds tests in sanity-hsm (253 and 256).\n\nSigned-off-by: Quentin Bouget <quentin.bouget@cea.fr>\nChange-Id: Id809ca9ab0ac3d4925b0692337f0694f286280df\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
